Researchers at Yahoo Labs in California have created a sensor that recognises the shape of your ear or any other body part you want to access .
Bodyprint was devised by Christian Holz, Senaka Buthpitiya, and Marius Knaust from the California-based Yahoo Labs .
The technology turns a standard touchscreen into a biometric scanner removing the need to specialist hardware such as infrared cameras or infrared cameras .
It also locks devices again as soon as a user moves away from their wallet .